{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e51-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3306"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3306"},"text":"§ 3306.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Encouragement of alternative dispute resolution","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Acquisition Regulation shall include a provision encouraging the use of alternative dispute resolution techniques to provide informal, expeditious, and inexpensive procedures for an offeror to consider using before filing a protest, prior to the award of a contract, of the exclusion of the offeror from the competitive range (or otherwise from further consideration) for that contract.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa1d3e52-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1816/c/2/F"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1816(c)(2)(F)","children":[],"tail":", (8), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4182"},"text":"134 Stat. 4182","children":[],"tail":", 4185.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa1d3e53-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa1d3e54-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idaa1d3e55-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The text